Thematic Analysis

To identify why participants considered the recounted videogame experience as art, we conducted inductive, reflexive thematic analysis as outlined by Braun and Clarke [1,2]. We analysed 172 participants responses, including the responses from 4 participants, who had no personal art experience with games to report, but nevertheless considered games as art. Among participants who responded that they did not consider games as art, they stated that they did not believe in `art (ID620), or likened games to a book of paintings, the book in itself isnt art, but it does contain many pictures of real art (ID540). These participants were subsequently not included in the thematic analysis. To gain a complete understanding of the participants reasoning, we analysed the entirety of participants written responses.

First, two coders individually read through the entire data set to familiarise themselves with the content, and noted down first ideas and observations. We decided to involve two coders, instead of one, as we assumed it will facilitate the theme generating process when more than one coder is familiar with the entire data. Second, the coders were asked to individually generate initial codes that represented the whole data set. Sentences formed the smallest coding units, to which multiple codes could be assigned. Codes were developed regarding the semantic content (i.e., what participants wrote) as well as on latent level (i.e., participants assumption underlining the semantic content). After discussing and combining the codes, both coders applied the coding scheme to the entire data set. This was done in order to facilitate finding illustrative quotes when reporting the themes later. The final 69 codes were collided, reevaluated, and merged to initial themes over several discussion sessions among the authors. During this process, the coders draw several thematic maps to consider the relations between the initial themes. Finally, one coder applied the initial themes to the entire data set to ensure the themes cover all instances, and drew a thematic map of the final themes. %Julia: draw and include thematic map

The inductive thematic analyses resulted in a final set of seven themes: Appreciating the Craft and Artisanship; Expressive Potential of Games; Awe and Wanderlust; Getting the Feels; Makes You Think; Room for Interpretation.
